-- Wigan Beats Warrington 30-16 in Super League Rugby Grand Final
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-10-05T19:05:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-05/wigan-beats-warrington-30-16-in-super-league-rugby-grand-final.html
The Wigan Warriors came from behind
to beat the Warrington Wolves 30-16 in rugby leagueâ€™s Super
League Grand Final.  Pat Richards scored a try and kicked five goals for the
Warriors, who outscored the Wolves 24-0 in the second half at
Old Trafford in Manchester. Darrell Goulding, Michael McIlorum,
Josh Charnley and Blake Green also touched down as Wigan claimed
its third Grand Final.  Wigan also won the rugby league Challenge Cup, becoming the
first team since St. Helens in 2006 to capture both titles in
the same season.  Joel Mohaghan, Simon Grix and Ben Westwood touched down for
Warrington, which lost the Grand Final for the second straight
year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
